<div class="home-img">
  <div class="container home-text">
    <h1>Create Rails app in 5 minutes!</h1>
    <h3>WALD converts your visual database schema into a <strong>working app</strong> with your own models migrations and database in minutes</h3>

    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between", style="width: 370px;">
      <div class="convert-now-class-div hvr-grow">
        <%= link_to "Convert Now", new_project_path, class: "btn convert-now-button" %>
      </div>

      <div class="how-it-works-class-div hvr-grow">
        <%= link_to "How It Works", "#howitworks", class: "btn how-it-works-button" %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="howitworks" class="steps text-center" >
  <h1 class="my-5">How does WALD work?</h1>
  <div class="row steps-with-icons">

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
      <i class="fas fa-database"></i>
      <div class="svg-wrapper">
        <svg height="60" width="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <rect class="shape" height="60" width="100%" />
        </svg>
        <div class="step-title mb-3"><a href="#drawSchema"><h4>Draw schema</h4></a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
      <div><i class="fas fa-file-upload"></i></div>
      <div class="svg-wrapper">
        <svg height="60" width="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <rect class="shape" height="60" width="100%" />
        </svg>
        <div class="step-title mb-3"><a href="#pasteXML"><h4>Paste XML code</h4></a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
      <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
      <div class="svg-wrapper">
        <svg height="60" width="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <rect class="shape" height="60" width="100%" />
        </svg>
        <div class="step-title mb-3"><a href="#checkOurWork"><h4>Check our work</h4></a></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
      <i class="fas fa-trophy"></i>
      <div class="svg-wrapper">
        <svg height="60" width="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <rect class="shape" height="60" width="100%" />
        </svg>
        <div class="step-title mb-3"><a href="#runYourApp"><h4>Run your app!</h4></a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>



<div id="drawSchema" class="lg-step-card d-inline-flex">
  <div class="card-text col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center pr-md-4 pr-lg-0">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-terminal terminal"></i>  Drawing database schema</h2>
    <p>Every app starts with the database schema. It's the skeleton that defines how the data is organized and how the relations among them are associated.</p>
    <p>Schema contains tables, columns, data types, relationships, primary keys, foreign keys, etc.</p>
    <p class="mt-3">Here are few important <i>rules</i> to follow to make our program works perfectly:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Choose the right data-type for each column</li>
      <li>Names matter! you should name your tables in plural, and your columns singular</li>
      <li>Think about the relations between your tables and use foreign keys to connect them.</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://kitt.lewagon.com/db/3411" class="purple-button-class mt-3" style="text-decoration: none;" >Create now</a>
  </div>

  <div class="lg-card-img col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center">
    <%= image_tag "schema1.png", style: "width: 80%; padding: 1rem;" %>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="pasteXML" class="lg-step-card-left d-inline-flex">
  <div class="lg-card-img col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center">
    <%= image_tag "files.svg", style: "width: 82%; margin-left: 15%;" %>
  </div>
  <div class="card-text col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center pr-md-4 pr-lg-0">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-terminal terminal"></i>  Copy XML schema code</h2>
    <p>Once you've finished create a logical schema, press the 'Save/Load' button.</p>
    <p>In the window that opened press 'Save XML' and copy the code that shows up in the output section.</p>
    <p class="mb-3"><i>That's all you need to make our app working for you!</i></p>
    <%= link_to "Start new project", new_project_path, class: "purple-button-class", style: "text-decoration: none;" %>
  </div>

</div>


<div id="checkOurWork" class="lg-step-card d-inline-flex">
  <div class="card-text col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center pr-md-4 pr-lg-0">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-terminal terminal"></i>  Check the results we've made for you</h2>
    <p>After your schema was converted you will be directed to a page with all the commands that was generated for your app.</p>
    <p>Before running the commands in your terminal, please check:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Models and Columns names should be singular.</li>
      <li>Data-types should match to the column.</li>
      <li>Foreign keys should have the ':references' addition.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-3">All the commands are editable so you could apply any changes if necessary.</p>
    <%= link_to "See your work", projects_path, class: "purple-button-class", style: "text-decoration: none;" %>
  </div>

  <div class="lg-card-img col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center">
    <%= image_tag "check_com.svg", style: "width: 65%; padding-left: 1.5rem;" %>
  </div>
</div>



<div id="runYourApp" class="lg-step-card-left d-inline-flex">
  <div class="lg-card-img col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center">
    <%= image_tag "man_laptop.svg", style: "width: 77%; margin-left: 15%;" %>
  </div>

  <div class="card-text col-sm-12 col-md-6 align-self-center pr-md-4 pr-lg-0">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-terminal terminal"></i>  Your app is ready to run!</h2>
    <p>Now it's time to run the commands that will generate your app.</p>
    <p>You can copy the 'rails new' command to your terminal and watch the magic happens!</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You could also create a new app by yourself and use the commands on the bottom to generate each model with matching migration by copying each comma to the terminal separately.</p>
    <%= link_to "Project page", projects_path, class: "purple-button-class", style: "text-decoration: none;" %>
  </div>
</div>

